    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>creamy tomato stock </strong>to the pot and cook for 1-2 min or until starting to thicken – this is your <strong>creamy tomato sauce</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>zested lemon[s]</strong> in half, then a squeeze of<strong> lemon </strong>juice into the sauce (not sure about citrus? Try using less!)</p>",
